  "aiHints": {
    "analysisContext": "AMR-WB storage format: '#!AMR-WB\\n'(9B: 23 21 41 4D 52 2D 57 42 0A) + frames. Each frame: 1-byte TOC (bits 7-4=mode 0-15, bit 3=quality, bits 2-0=padding) + payload. AMR-WB frame sizes by mode: mode0=17B, mode1=23B, mode2=32B, mode3=36B, mode4=40B, mode5=46B, mode6=50B, mode7=58B, mode8=60B, SID=5B, NO_DATA=0B. Sample rate: 16000 Hz (wideband), 20ms per frame = 320 samples. Total frames × 20ms = duration. AMR-WB is used for HD Voice (VoLTE) in LTE networks.",
    "suggestedInspections": [
      "Verify '#!AMR-WB\\n' at offset 0: 23 21 41 4D 52 2D 57 42 0A",
      "Read first TOC byte at offset 9: bits 7-4 = mode (0-8 valid), bit 3 = quality",
      "Mode 8 (23.85 kbps) is highest quality AMR-WB mode",
      "Frame count × 20ms = total audio duration",
      "Compare with AMR-NB ('#!AMR\\n', 6B, 8000 Hz) vs AMR-WB ('#!AMR-WB\\n', 9B, 16000 Hz)"
    ]
  },
  "software": [
